OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FThe war in Iran has sent shockwaves
OL,8,Fthrough the global economy, with
OL,9,FTehran using the Strait of Hormuz as a
OL,10,Fway of causing chaos in the oil and
OL,11,Fgas markets, putting intense pressure
OL,12,Fon Donald Trump.
OL,14,FBefore the conflict, a barrel of oil
OL,15,Ftraded for between $60-70, but since
OL,16,Ffighting broke out, it has hovered
OL,17,Faround $100.
OL,19,FA similar story is true for liquefied
OL,20,Fnatural gas, a commodity the UK is
OL,21,Fheavily reliant on.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FThe dramatic uptick in the cost of two
OL,8,Fof the world's most used energy
OL,9,Fsources has caused chaos in the global
OL,10,Feconomy, with warnings that the
OL,11,Fconflict could increase inflation
OL,12,Facross the world.
OL,14,FIn the UK, petrol and diesel have
OL,15,Frisen sharply, and energy companies
OL,16,Fhave warned bills could rise
OL,17,Fdramatically as a result of the war.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FThe government has chaired emergency
OL,8,Fmeetings discussing how the war could
OL,9,Fhave a dramatic impact on the cost of
OL,10,Fliving, just as inflation was
OL,11,Fbeginning to stabilise.
OL,13,FThe key driver of all of this chaos
OL,14,Fhas been Iran's decision to close the
OL,15,Fcritical Strait of Hormuz shipping
OL,16,Flane.
OL,18,FBut why is the Strait of Hormuz so
OL,19,Fimportant, and how could prolonged
OL,20,Fdisruption affect the global economy
OL,21,Fand UK bills?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FWhat is the Strait of Hormuz?
OL,9,FThe Strait of Hormuz is a narrow
OL,10,Fpassage that connects the Persian Gulf
OL,11,Fto the Gulf of Oman.
OL,13,FIran controls the entire northern
OL,14,Fside, effectively allowing it to wield
OL,15,Fthe strait as a geopolitical
OL,16,Fchokepoint.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31005
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FThe strait ` almost 100 miles long and
OL,8,F21 miles wide at its narrowest point `
OL,9,Fallows some of the world's largest
OL,10,Fvessels to transport a fifth of global
OL,11,Foil and gas supplies.
OL,13,FShips departing to or from Kuwait,
OL,14,FBahrain, Qatar, Iraq and the United
OL,15,FArab Emirates must pass through the
OL,16,Fstrait to reach open waters.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31006
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FCrude oil from Saudi Arabia and Iran
OL,8,Fis also transported through the
OL,9,Fpassage, but they have other ports
OL,10,Fwhich can be used in case the strait
OL,11,Fis closed.
OL,13,FWhen it comes to moving oil, the
OL,14,Fstrait is actually much narrower than
OL,15,Fits 21-mile official width.
OL,17,FThe navigable shipping lanes for
OL,18,Fmassive supertankers are only about
OL,19,Ftwo miles wide in each direction,
OL,20,Frequiring vessels to pass through both
OL,21,FIranian and Omani territorial waters.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31007
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FAny disruption to traffic through the
OL,8,FStrait of Hormuz is, in turn, highly
OL,9,Fdisruptive to the oil trade.
OL,11,FWhat has Iran said about the Strait
OL,12,Fsince the conflict sparked again?
OL,14,FThe Strait of Hormuz is effectively
OL,15,Fclosed.
OL,17,FIran has carried out attacks on ships
OL,18,Fpassing through and vowed to continue
OL,19,Fthis, which has led to shipping
OL,20,Fcompanies suspending operations in the
OL,21,Farea.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FIran has also threatened to mine the
OL,8,Fstrait if its energy infrastructure is
OL,9,Fstruck by the US and Israel.
OL,11,FA trickle of ships has gotten through,
OL,12,Fand Iran insists the crucial waterway
OL,13,Fremains open ` just not to the US,
OL,14,FIsrael or their allies.
OL,16,FTrump has issued numerous threats to
OL,17,FIran, attempting to force it to reopen
OL,18,Fthe strait, but so far, none have
OL,19,Fworked.
OL,21,FWhat is the disruption?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FTanker traffic has dropped sharply, as
OL,8,Fglobal shippers suspend operations in
OL,9,Fthe area until further notice.
OL,11,F"No one wants to navigate it, and
OL,12,Fthere's no insurer who's willing to
OL,13,Fstand behind any transport going
OL,14,Fthrough there right now," said Tom
OL,15,FGoldsby, logistics chairman in the
OL,16,FSupply Chain Management Department at
OL,17,Fthe University of Tennessee.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31010
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,F"Those ships that got stuck in the
OL,8,FGulf are not going anywhere. ...
OL,9,FThere's also a whole host of ships
OL,10,Fthat were heading into the Gulf to
OL,11,Freplace them, and of course they're
OL,12,Fanchored or going elsewhere now."
OL,14,FWho will be hit hardest?
OL,16,FIran and the Gulf states have been hit
OL,17,Fhardest by the closing of the Strait
OL,18,Fof Hormuz, with a huge amount of their
OL,19,Feconomies reliant on it for exports.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31011
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FIt is also bad news for the countries
OL,8,Fthat receive these exports, which are
OL,9,Fnow being forced to look further
OL,10,Fafield for their energy.
OL,12,FNations like India, South Korea and
OL,13,FChina rely heavily on exports from the
OL,14,FGulf.
OL,16,FThe Energy Information Administration
OL,17,F(EIA) estimates that 84% of the crude
OL,18,Foil and 83% of the liquefied natural
OL,19,Fgas that moved through the Strait of
OL,20,FHormuz in 2024 went to Asian markets.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31012
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FBut this doesn't mean the rest of the
OL,8,Fworld won't be impacted, with the
OL,9,Fprice of gas and oil shooting up
OL,10,Fmassively on global markets.
OL,12,FWith big players like China and India
OL,13,Fable to put in enormous orders with
OL,14,Fother regions, they will force smaller
OL,15,Fcountries to pay higher prices.
OL,17,FThe head of the International Energy
OL,18,FAgency (IEA) has said that the global
OL,19,Feconomy faces a "major, major threat"
OL,20,Fbecause of the Iran war.
OL,26,@{D@QOU{D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31013
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FFatih Birol said the crisis in the
OL,8,FMiddle East has had a worse impact on
OL,9,Foil than the two oil shocks of the
OL,10,F1970s combined, and a worse effect on
OL,11,Fgas than the Russia-Ukraine war.
OL,13,FWhat could it mean for UK energy bills?
OL,15,FThe price of petrol and diesel has
OL,16,Falready risen in the UK as a result of
OL,17,Fthe conflict, but energy bills have
OL,18,Fbeen shielded by the energy price cap.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31014
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FIt is currently locked in place until
OL,8,F30 June, but energy bosses have warned
OL,9,Fthat price rises are "inescapable."
OL,11,FThe chief executive of Centrica, which
OL,12,Fowns British Gas, told the BBC that
OL,13,Fglobal oil supplies are down 20%
OL,14,Fbecause of the conflict.
OL,16,FChris O'Shea said: "Cornwall Insight,
OL,17,FI think, have predicted that there's
OL,18,Fgoing to be an increase in prices. If
OL,19,Fit stays as it is then I think that's
OL,20,Finescapable."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31015
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774296676
OL,3,CWhy is the Strait of Hormuz so vital
OL,4,Cand how could disruption affect UK
OL,5,Cbills?
OL,7,FThe government has also chaired an
OL,8,Femergency Cobra meeting examining how
OL,9,Fto address the looming cost-of-living
OL,10,Fcrisis as a result of the Iran war.
OL,12,FOn top of an expected increase in
OL,13,Fenergy bills, there are warnings of
OL,14,Fsignificant food inflation.
OL,16,FFood producers heavily rely on oil for
OL,17,Ftransport and tractor costs, while the
OL,18,Fvast majority of the cost of
OL,19,Ffertiliser production is based on the
OL,20,Fprice of gas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
